value.value: An analogue of the antineoplastic benzoquinone antibiotic geldanamycin. Alvespimycin binds to HSP90, a chaperone protein that aids in the assembly, maturation and folding of proteins. Subsequently, the function of Hsp90 is inhibited, leading to the degradation and depletion of its client proteins such as kinases and transcription factors involved with cell cycle regulation and signal transduction.

label.value: Parathyroid Gland Mixed Cell Type Adenoma

value.value: A parathyroid gland adenoma that contains a mixture of neoplastic cells (chief cells, oncocytes, and clear cells).
A solitary fibrous tumor characterized by the presence of areas of abrupt transition to high grade sarcoma.
A rare condition characterized by the development of a carcinoma in a pre-existing craniopharyngioma.

A renal cell carcinoma with eosinophilic cytoplasm and high nuclear grade.  Granular cells can be seen in any subtype of renal cell carcinoma, including conventional clear cell carcinoma.  This term does not represent a specific subtype of renal cell carcinoma and should no longer be used.
A paraganglioma that arises from and is confined to the carotid body.
An adenoma characterized by the presence of papillary epithelial patterns.

A benign ovarian epithelial tumor. It has been described in mice and rats and is rare in other animal species. Morphologically it is characterized by the presence of tubular structures and interstitial stroma.
A wild-type zebrafish line that is polymorphic relative to the Tubingen line.
A wild-type zebrafish line.

A zebrafish line established from a group of 25 crosses between individual AB and Tubingen fish. The progeny of two crosses that lacked recessive embryonic phenotypes through 5 or 6 days of development were selected as founders of two distinct lethal free lines that were designated TAB-5 and TAB-14.
A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was obtained from an area east of Calcutta in a district called Nadia.
A wild-type zebrafish line.
A designation used to describe a wild-type zebrafish line that is of unknown stock.
A type B1 thymoma which is characterized by an aggressive clinical course (capsular invasion, infiltration of the surrounding tissues) and can metastasize.
This gene is involved in both the binding and transport of retinol and the thyroid hormone thyroxine.

The mesylate form of almitrine, a diphenylmethylpiperazine derivative and respiratory stimulant that can be used to improve oxygenation. Upon systemic administration, almitrine targets, binds to and activates the peripheral chemoreceptors located on the carotid bodies. This enhances respiration and increases arterial oxygen tension while decreasing arterial carbon dioxide tension.

Human TTR wild-type allele is located in the vicinity of 18q12.1 and is approximately 7 kb in length. This allele, which encodes transthyretin protein, plays a role in the stabilization and transport of thyroxine and retinol. Mutations in the gene are associated with hyperthyroxinemia and amyloidosis types 1 and 7.
Transthyretin (147 aa, ~16 kDa) is encoded by the human TTR gene. This protein is involved in both the binding and transport of retinol and thyroxine.
The log base E value of argument X.

A zebrafish line derived from the mating of two lines, A and B, obtained in Albany, Oregon. Haploid offspring from individual females of the AB line were screened for healthy, good looking embryos. Females obtained from the screening were used to breed future generations by crossing them to unselected males. This procedure reduced the number of lethal mutations so that this line can be used for parthenogenesis.
The quality of being similar or corresponding in position or value or structure or function.

A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was collected in Darjeeling, India in 1987. This line has been maintained through inbreeding. It is used for gene mapping due to the presence of several polymorphic markers.

Also known as well-differentiated thymic carcinoma, atypical thymoma, or epithelial thymoma, this type of thymoma displays morphologic characteristics of a well-differentiated carcinoma.  The majority of cases occur in the anterior mediastinum as Masaoka stage II or stage III tumors.  It is almost always invasive, it recurs frequently, and metastasizes in approximately 20% of the cases.
A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was obtained from Ekkwill Breeders (Florida).
A wild-type zebrafish line that is a hybrid of the Hong Kong and AB wild-type lines.
A wild-type zebrafish line that is extinct.
A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was obtained from a fish dealer in Hong Kong, China.
A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was obtained from an expedition to Darjeeling, India.
A wild-type zebrafish line, the stock of which was obtained from an Indonesian fish dealer.
Surgical creation of an external opening into the jejunum.
A wild-type zebrafish line that is currently available from the National BioResource Project, Zebrafish, NRBP/Brain Science Institute, RIKEN.

A rare, usually aggressive primary thymic carcinoma, characterized by a syncytial growth of undifferentiated carcinoma cells and the presence of a lymphoplasmacytic infiltrate.  More than 40% of cases are associated with Epstein-Barr virus infection.
